commit.message:
Makes the package arch independent

With ARCH_INDEPENDENT option the package is considered compatible on any
architecture.
ARCH_INDEPEDENT is available on 3.14 released on March 2019. Version 3.16
was released on Nov 2019. Small difference and we will require 3.16 on
the upcoming Qt6 version.

Fixes https://github.com/lxqt/lxqt-menu-data/issues/17.

commit.message:
Add science category (#5)

* menu: change "Education" to "Education & Science"

Current menus do not cover the `Science` category. It is generally not
an issue as most applications that have category `Science` (ex:
Libreoffice Math, GeoGebra) also have category `Education`. However,
some applications (ex: Picoscope [1]) have cateogory `Science` only and
not `Education`, and thus they are classified as "Other".

A considered fix is adding an "Education" submenu using
`lxqt-education.directory`. However, that directory uses the same icon
(`applications-science`) as `lxqt-science-math.directory`, and it cannot
switch to `applications-education` icon, as the latter is not a standard
icon name [2] and is missing from many icon themes [3]. As a result,
users will see two submenus with the same icon and many common
applications.

As we have full control of menu-related files after relevant LXQt
components are migrated [4], we can change menu files to include the
`Science` category.

`lxqt-education.directory` is preserved for backward compatibility. It
may be used in some custom menu files.

[1] https://www.picotech.com/
[2] https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xdg/default-icon-theme/-/blob/master/spec/icon-naming-spec.xml
[3] https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Comparison_of_icon_sets#Categories
[4] https://github.com/lxqt/lxqt/issues/1679

* Setup translations

commit.message:
Add CMake package file

Per docs [1], `ARCH_INDEPENDENT` can be added to
write_basic_package_version_file(). It needs CMake >= 3.14, and no
other LXQt packages use that, so I skip it as well.

[1] https://cmake.org/cmake/help/latest/module/CMakePackageConfigHelpers.html
